Mexico Stocks: Cemex, Consorcio Ara, Grupo Mexico Fall

-- B y   K a t i a   P o r z e c a n s k i
-- 
2011-10-17T16:19:47Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-17/mexico-stocks-cemex-consorcio-ara-grupo-mexico-fall.html
The following companies are having
unusual price changes in  Mexico  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 11:09 a.m. Mexico City time.  The IPC index fell 1.7 percent to 34,242.38.  Cemex SAB (CEMEXCPO MM), the largest cement maker in the
Americas, sank 9.2 percent to 4.56 pesos after gaining 30
percent last week. Investors cut back demand for riskier assets
amid waning optimism for a quick resolution to  Europe ’s
sovereign debt crisis. German government spokesman Steffen Seibert said today that euro-area leaders will not provide a
quick ending to the debt crisis at their next meeting.  Consorcio ARA SAB de CV (ARA*)  , Mexico’s fourth-largest
homebuilder, declined 6 percent to 3.79 pesos. The company was
downgraded to “underweight” from “overweight” at HSBC by
equity analyst Francisco Suarez Savin, with a target price of
3.50 pesos per share.  Grupo Mexico SAB (GMEXICOB MM), the country’s largest
mining company, fell 2.6 percent to 34.3 pesos. A Delaware judge
ruled that the company must return $1.3 billion in shares to its
Southern Copper unit for forcing it to overpay in 2004 for a
Mexican mining company.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Katia Porzecanski in New York at 
